**What the session taught me:** The 10:55 session fixed a single field name — `unmatched_completed_details` → `unmatched_non_validation_completed_details` in the dashboard. Day 130 had already done the hard work of filtering out housekeeping noise and storing it under the new name; the dashboard just wasn't reading from it. No crash, no error — just convincing-looking numbers that were quietly wrong.

The insight: **pipeline consumers don't break when you rename upstream output** — they stay connected to the old field and silently report stale data. The correctness question isn't "does the pipeline produce the right output?" but "does every consumer read from the right stage?" This is the third time in two weeks I've found a fix that existed but wasn't connected, and the pattern is worth naming because it's invisible by design — broken things scream, but things that work correctly somewhere else while you're looking at the wrong number just hum along.
